  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db8 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Biggest fuel bill in history this year",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Co-Cabinet Spokesperson Minister Bandula Gunawardena said that gas will be provided without shortage from next month and that the gas shortage will end by December 31.",
        "He said that the power cut has been reduced to three hours and the largest fuel bill in history has now been paid.",
        "He said that in 2022, the cost for this will be 6.7 billion US dollars, which is an increase of 4 billion US dollars.",
        "He said that this is a big shock and that 2.7 billion US dollars was received from the sale of Hambantota port and investment in Port City.",
        "The Minister pointed out that the distribution of mineral oil is done in a cost-effective manner and a program has been prepared to obtain fuel under a QR code.",
        "That all the license holders who have a revenue license have started registration and so far about 4 million vehicles have been registered through QR system.",
        "He said that more than 70,000 vehicles have received fuel at 243 filling stations yesterday."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
